<br>
For just about any guild that can get that far, most of the questable stuff in air is crap ( with the exception of a few hybrid haste items, etc ).<br>
<br>
Most of that quest stuff ( again with the exception of epic drops ), is just &quot;grats delete button &quot;.<br>
<br>
The zone is gruelling, takes a significant investment in time, etc etc.  For this reason, guilds dont just &quot; pop up and do air &quot; like they do hate and fear.  They generally go as far as they need to go for their membership ( to accomplish whatever they had in mind ).<br>
<br>
Soo..<br>
<br>
If a guild is going to isle 7, 99.999 percent it is because they have some mage(s) who need the piece.  Bringing another out of guild mage to roll against your in guild mage simply isnt an option when you are looking at the time investment to get there.  If a guild doesnt have mages who need, there is very little point in actually going that far due to the time moving from isle to isle takes in air.  <br>
<br>
Soo.. Guild raids that go to isle for mage epic will almost always have mages who need, and guild raids that dont have mages who need wont go that high.  Its extremely unfortunate, but thats how it works.<br>
<br>
It can be done on open raids... Pimm led several very successful open raids way back before everyone was level 60 with Skyshrine / Kael quest armor and epics.  Cicely lead an open raid.  I think the mage community could do it, if 2-3 mages get together and try to bring a group or 2 each.. of people who have been to PoA etc.<br>
